hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
The hotel is not bad. Positive: good breakfast, we had a room for 3 with 2 separate spaces (connected rooms), I appreciated it. Bathroom was big and nice. Well connected with metro line 1. Good quality shampoo and conditioner.
Negative: the area is not very nice, the receptionist was not very friendly, the hotel is a 3 star hotel, not 4….

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Room, bathroom too small. Too hot in the room. AC not working. Breakfast for A 4 star hotel very poor.

At arrival your staff at rhe reception info to pay citytax. I told him i want to pay cash. I gave him €50 and he told me i will get the change at check out so i request a receipt. He inform me he cannot give receipt. I asked how can i proof that i gave you €50 he than shook his shoulder. So he started the machine so i can swipe my creditcard only he didnt mentioned any amount in the machine. When i told him he shook again with his shoulder.
This experience gave me A very bad feeling.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
My family of 4 was very happy to stay in Paris for a week as the hotel is very close to the metro station and other public transport (trams, buses).
In the adjacent streets we found many bistros and restaurants, a supermarket and many types of shops.
The metro line is ideal for visiting most of the major sights in Paris.
The hotel is clean and well run, the rooms and common areas are not very large, but this is not the aim when visiting Paris and the positive points of the hotel outweigh the few negative points.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Great service, comfortable room, great breakfast and close to Metro line 1 in Paris. Also close to other restaurants to choose from during your visit. I do recommend this hotel if you want to be close to the metro and restaurants.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
The hotel offers a cute and nice atmosphere. But there was a few drawbacks.

The room came without air condition, unlike what the information beforehand said. The ventilation itselv was also poor, so we had to open the windows pretty often to get freash air in.

The hotel was also a bit dirty. Dust and piles of dust many places. Plates not always clean at the breakfast area.

The rooms was also a bit small with to much furniture for it’s size.

Will choose another hotel next time in Paris.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Rooms very very small you cannot move around just sleeping so as breakfast very poor, however staff very professional and caring for the customers.The position of the hotel is excellent as very closed to the Metro.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Very small basic room, no luxuries. Carpet was quite stained, soap dispenser kept falling off bathroom wall. No replenishment of tea/coffee/milk or water.
Asked receptionist who said I had to put the hanger outside bedroom door to indicate I wanted room made up. Did this but still no replenishment of basics.
Kettle was plugged in and set up inside wardrobe which was odd so clothes would end up all damp and steamy.

Breakfast was very basic compared to other 4 star experiences we’ve had.

Lift was tiny and fitted 2 people.

Room very noisy, walls paper thin. Had trouble settling at night and getting to sleep.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: great breakfast! diverse choices, we really enjoy it. room (incl. bath room) is clean. staff are friendly and helpful. close to metro station. good location with shops and restaurants nearby. we have good stay!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: A good choise, near Metro, friendly staff, excellent breakfast, cosy, the rooms are small but with all necessary items inside. Very comfortable bed and pilows. The water was offered by the hotel. We enjoyed the vacation!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Staff was helpful, customer service was great. Room was of a smaller size but was ok for a short stay. Location was convenient, easy to go to downtown on a train, down the street was a nice restaurant Belair.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The hotel was wonderful. The rooms were small but expected. The staff were super friendly and nice. Downside is that it is a little father away to "Downtown" Paris although it is located really close to the main metro lines and bus. It is farther away so that it makes it hard to go back to the hotel during the day because you'll have to take the metro back and forth. Good if you aren't going to stay in the hotel too long and just there for sleep.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: We lodged in Best Western Plus Paris Nation and it was a very good option to visit Paris since the relation quality/price is really amazing. Metro to Arc du Triomphe is direct and just 25 minuts to go. It is highly recommended for families.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: This Best Western location may seem on the outskirts of Paris, but because it is very close to the Porte de Vincennes stop, it was super accessible to Paris. If that is a concern to you, it really was super easy to get in and out of Paris and its main attractions. The breakfast served at the hotel was also so delicious! Baguette, fresh eggs, fruit, and other pastries kept us full well past the lunch hour. It was definitely worth our while having the breakfast included because it was less work for us to figure out where and what to eat, and it was delicious! All the staff at the hotel were incredibly helpful and kind. Some even offered to book transportation on their own cellphones for us. If we travel to Paris again, this is the place we will go!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: We visited Paris and Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation from 13/08 to 17/08. The location was very good due to its connection to most of the metro lines. In addition our room was very cosy (cute and practical. I would recommend more careful cleaning. The breakfast had absolutely everything. Henry at the reception was the best. He helped us with his tips and made our days with his cheerful mood and his politeness.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Stay away! Save yourself the hassle. We ended up leaving and staying elsewhere. It’s dirty, small and a/c was not working during the hottest time of the year. The front desk clerk was in our room at 3am trying to fix the a/c but was not able to. Sleepless night and the next day was shot because we were exhausted.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Great stay, The rooms were decent, had everything you need for a city trip. The bathroom had a nice shower and the people at the reception were very nice snd helpfull. Metro line 1 is around the corner. We ate in the neighborhood near metrostation Nation in multiple restaurants which had great prices for good food and there was always somebody who spoke English.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Good sized family suite for Paris, very near public transport, main Paris metro line 1 only 2 minutes away, supermarket around the corner, nice and very friendly staff, free candy available in the lobby-nice touch if you are travelling with children...

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: My family enjoyed our stay at the hotel. The location is not bad for touring Paris with a couple of major metro stations nearby. The room rate was reasonable. The room was smaller than what we are used to but we are glad they had a family room with two queen beds. The breakfast was wonderful, the room and bathroom is clean, and the staff is friendly. Our only complaint was the lift was broken when we got there so taking our luggage up to our 3rd floor room was a challenge, and it didn't get fixed for another couple of days.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Highly recommended, at only 2 minutes walking distance from Port de Vincennes of Paris underground.
Clean and quite rooms with a modern look.

Good continental breakfast served from 7:00 am.
Daily change of towels.

Friendly staff with a 24-hours reception.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The room was ridiculously small, the doors ill fitting so the night light in the corridor came through the door all night and the first night we had really noisy people in the room next to us until the very early hours of the morning. And the curtains did not fit so more light came into room from the street lights. Thin walls and ill fitting doors did not help. The carpet on the stairs although hoovered each were filthy. It was the staff and the breakfasts that saved this rating. Staff were very helpful and the breakfast was fantastic, without them I would have scored the hotel as poor.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Very nice hotel. Metro station is 2 min walk fom the hotel, from which you can get to all top attractions. Staff were very nice and helpful. Room was clean and big enough for two xl suitcases. Overall would recommend for your stay in Paris.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Nice BW boutique hotel style.
Location is perfect - 5 mn walk to the metro line 1 and to the Tram. That allows you to go to center of Paris or to Champs Elysees in less than 20 minutes.
The service is just perfect.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Overall Hotel was good.
- Reception was friendly and helpfull
- Breakfast was fresh and enough and good
-Floor in the room was not one day cleaned
- Coffee and was not filled up.
Parking is 20 min by walk. Appr. 35 eur 24h

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: First time visit to Paris and I must say everything about it was lovely. I booked it for my wife's birthday which was a surprise. And the guys at the hotel did everything to make this very pleasant. The metro is only round the corner which is wicked!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The area is far from the city but it was okay because it is located near the metro, accessibilty is super and the breakfast was also good. It was also quite and every was clean and neat. Staff were very pleasant to talk to.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Amazing Hotel, very close to the Metro, has a big plentiful Breakfast, clean, modern looking, normal room has space for 2 adults with 3 suitcases, has a safe and a mini-fridge and with a friendly staff!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: My 3rd stay at this property. Although the rooms are quite small staff are very friendly and location of the hotel is very convenient. ADHOC/ FIT rates are quite high. Wish hotel would offer more food and beverages.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Hotel is nice, staff is helpful, especially I believe Omar who has helped us a lot with luggage and figuring out a way to the airport after a check out.

Rooms are good, we stayed in a suite and cannot complain, nice size bathroom for Paris standards.

Only issue was sound - we could hear other people’s conversations.
Area isn’t the cosiest but connection is great - metro is 2 min away!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
The hotel is really close to the metro stop and you can go to the city center in 15-20 minutes.
Very polite employees and eager to help us with everything.
Definitely we will come back next time.
Thank you very much.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Very bad place to enjoy paris, bad attention for the front desk manager, nothing works, no AC, damaged fridge, they do not put soap, in the bathroom, bad location, they lie about shuttle airport, they dont have

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
My second stay at this hotel. Quite convenient location. Rooms are quite small, but sufficient for one person and for a short stay. Very friendly and helpful staff.
Upgrade to next category junior suite is bit too expensive.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The hotel staff were very friendly, bed was super cosy. I'm giving this hotel 3 stars as the rooms were very tight to get around and the breakfast wasn't the best considering how much euros it was per day. Much better going out for breakfast and getting something from the local bakery's around

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Stayed here for several nights. Front desk / customer service is excellent. Nice lounge area as well. Neighborhood isn't the greatest, but very close to subway. Rooms are a bit small and in need of an update. Good for the budget traveler.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The room size is quite small but it has everything you need. The location is excellent and the staffs were very pleasant and responsive to any quires. One of our rooms experienced electricity blackout daily for a short period but the staff managed to solve the issue quickly.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Very helpful staff. Good location with lots of restaurants nearby and well connected by metro and buses.
The hotel was very clean.
Small rooms with a tiny elevator.
But overall I am greatly satisfied with my stay.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Small cosy hotel. Clean, staff is polite and helpful. Our room was too hot, we did put the AC to the minimum, but it might have been broken. But window with the cute french balcony helped. Room is small, but this is France, it should be. As it is not far away from the main street, be ready for some big city noises (tram, bus, sirens etc), but this is big city life. Location was wonderful, metro 1 is 3 minutes away. Neighbourhood was friendly, more families.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Good value, great rooms, great breakfast and good location. Friendly and helpful staff. Amenities are good for a Paris city center hotel. My family and I enjoyed our stay very much. Easy and quick access to main Paris attractions.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: I really enjoyed my stay in the hotel. The staff was very kind and helpful. The bedroom was big enough for the three of us. I liked the breakfast very much. Even though the hotel wasn't in the center it was very well connected by the metro, tram and bus.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Hotel easy to find and one min to the metro and on Line 1 that has most of the sights to get off and explore as 15 mins into the city as location of hotel is very good. Staff are friendly as room is very small and compact and has you need. Could hear people in other rooms walking above us as the had kids and they were running around from early morning so did no get a great sleep other than that a good stay.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: This was a great little hotel on a tiny street but next to the Port de Vincennes for easy access to the Metro. It was right around the corner from all the noise but we didn't hear a thing. It was clean and the staff were very nice. We found most everywhere people treated us with disdain with they realized we were American (it would help if we learned French I know) but the people here were very kind and helped us find good restaurants and gave great advice. The rooms were small but very clean. Had a breakfast in the lobby that looked good but we didn't use it. Internet worked great. Has tiny elevator but that's normal. Cute little winding staircase that needs new flooring. Overall a quaint and reasonably priced place to sleep after touring!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: While i only stayed for 1 night at the Best Western Plus it was super comfortable. Staff is very nice and attentive, helped me with figuring my way around the city. Definitely coming back eventually. The rooms are nice, not large but very comfortable and inviting.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Stayed in August for 2 nights. Family with 2 teens.
Hotel needs an update and some maintenance. You can see humidity signs in the bathroom and the bathroom door handle felt during our stay but we did not mind. We were only using the room to sleep.
Price was good. Very close to the metro. Very quiet in the room and overall location. Felt safe at all time. We cannot say the room was spacious but we had the family room and the kids had their own room, that was very appreciated. Staff was friendly and helpful.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The room was very clean and the service was great. The rooms are small as is the hotel, but the location was great and in a non-tourist area. It was just a couple of minutes to the metro and about 15 minutes into to the city. The staff was knowledgeable and friendly.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Perfect location for both business and leisure trips. Metro (subway) bus and Tram are a couple of minutes from this hotel. The manager and the staff are very nice and committed to help you in any circumstance :)

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The weird thing about this hotel is that you need to deposit your room key at the reception each time you step out of the hotel. I have never seen this kind of odd rule at any hotel across the globe. The room was also very small. The TV channel selections did not have English channels either.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The rooms are small but perfect. If I had one negative it would be that they could do with fans to help with the heat. The staff are wonderful and beyond helpful. I would stay here again without question.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Its' a good stay at the hotel and the staff can understand English :). clean rooms. Hotel is situated claim place but accesses to all type of transportation system in Paris by five min walk. you can enjoy western food there; breakfast. the only bad thing that room is disturbed by other room noises, even TV sound.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Room - clean but extremely small
Staff - friendly and polite
Breakfast - very small area with limited choices
View - poor
Location - poor
Value for money - poor
Facilities - poor (asked for ice and none available)
Wouldn't recommend!

Really confused why this needs to be 200 characters!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
It was a nice hotel and the hotel receptionist was friendly besides the room was clean everyday and I did not face any difficulty during my stay
I would recommend your hotel to my friends and colleagues

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The room had met our expectations, and although small as it is normally in Paris, it was clean and had a spacious shower. The staff was kind and welcoming and the breakfast was great. It isn't at the best area especially since it’s a bit distant, though there is a metro station nearby.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Excellent stay at the Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel.
Great to access Paris city centre as well as Disneyland Paris with the Metro and Nation station not too far away.
The hotel itself is a small hotel but exactly what we wanted for the trip.
Hotel staff were very polite and always helpful if there was anything that you needed.
We needed European plugs as well as an iron and ironing board. The staff were more than helpful in sorting this out for us and making sure that we had a great stay.
The breakfast in the morning was lovely, great range of food to start the day and something we enjoyed.
Would definitely recommend this hotel if you are staying in Paris. Value for money 100%.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
No bothering during the whole stay. Things went smooth.
Just the noise of other guests, loud voices in the early mornings and late night. And a review here should not be by obligation more than 200 characters! :D

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Hotel personnel was outstanding and extremely attentive.
Rooms where oldish and not kept as clean as one would wish/expect.
Internet connection was really bad.
Breakfast was nice and available even for "early birds"

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: This nice small hotel located in Paris is 5 mn walking distance from the metro and the ‘tramway’. All hotel employees are nice and ready to help you when you need. You’ll find restaurants and shops near the hotel.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
We stay there for a week on Dec'18. My husband got a job to do there for a week. Yannick was the 1st person welcoming us that night. And he's the one who helped me carry my kid to the room while my husband havent arrive yet to the hotel. My kids love him. I even miss the bfast buffet there...i wish one day i can come back and stay there. Thank u Yannick and the rest of fnb and housekeeping team!

Love, Ayu
Jakarta

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
The hotel is located just few steps from the metro station and you can be quickly in any part of the city. Nearby hotel there are supermarkets and several good places to eat.
Everything in this hotel was supertiny: from the elevator where only 1 person can fit, to hotel corridors where you can struggle with a bigger suitcase, to room that just fits 1 double bed and not much else. The room was clean and warm though.
My biggest complaint goes to the cleaning staff in the morning. I stayed over a weekend and went out on both Friday and Saturday night so had a long sleep on Saturday and Sunday mornings. Well, almost. The cleaning staff was so loud, chitchatting in the corridors, that you couldn't really sleep! Not professional at all.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
I chose this hotel as I got a really good deal from a website that provided us with a superior room and macaroons! Yum.
The journey from the airport into Paris, if travelling by train and metro, is a little tiresome and long winded with all the changes, however, the metro is literally two seconds round the corner from the hotel and the main line to get you to all the places you need in central Paris. That is why I chose this hotel due to its location.
It isn’t central by any means but only ten to fifteen mins by metro to anywhere really.
The standard of the hotel is good and the breakfast offered was adequate and lovely enough for us to fill up ready for the day ahead. The decor is relaxing and modern and we enjoyed it. The best bacon I’ve tasted for a long time!!
Another lovely touch if you have toddlers, is the sweet station and kids corner.
Yes the rooms are small and so is the lift, but do you know what, if you can’t all fit in do it in two separate journeys. It is an old French building and they have done their best with the facilities the building allows space for.
We found the rooms and hotel decor to be tastefully furnished and the beds lovely and comfy.
We had a lovely meal just across from the entrance to the metro at a Pizzeria and the food was lovely.
Overall it was a lovely stay and we chose this hotel due to the fact that it wouldn’t be as long a journey back to the airport on our return home.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Travelling with my father in Paris. This hotel is off the beaten path but easily accessible by subway.
Staff was awesome. Very accommodating. Allowed my father to keep his medication in their fridge and kept our ice pack frozen. Very hospitable. Definitely recommend if you ok with subway travel which is safe and easy to do. Restaurants and markets close by.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: This hotel locates near to Art De Tromps and shopping malls, it has nice and clean room. Everything is perfect and new. The cafe food is delicious. The service is good and the stuff are quite friendly.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
The lift was very small,
Access to the hotel wifi too complicated and with problems
Very poor breakfast of food
Relax area and Breakfast area not adequate mostly the relax/business area
children very noisy in reception and lift

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: It a very clean hotel, with really friendly and helpful reception staff, rooms are basic, but got every thing you need with big stand up shower with lots of hot water. We payed for breakfast too be included and we found breakfast great, lots to choose from, including hot food, but the same everyday, so this would get boring if you were staying for a longtime. The lady who manages the breakfast service is lovely and really helpful and couln't do enough for you, so thank you to her. The hotel round the corner from lots of places to eat and supermarkets, so this handy. It also around the corner from the main metro line so really easy to get to the main attractions and a metro and a train to get to the airport so quite cheap to travel. Their was only 2 negative things about this hotel, if u get a rubbish view, and told u cant change rooms, and not enough hanging space in the bathroom. But this would not stop me staying at this hotel again if i was in Paris.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The hotel was allright for one night, but the room was really extremely tiny. One could hardly move, and there wasn't even the space to place the suitcase. Besides people were nice and the standards were sufficient. Breakfast could have included a bit more choice.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
We are currently staying at this hotel and really like it. It is a little far from the center of Paris but there is a Metro station one of the major lines right around the corner. Super easy to get anywhere. It is a quite neighborhood too. The beds are comfortable. The staff has been great.

Our only criticism would be with the back “hangout” area. There isn’t covering. There should be. 2 reasons - 1) there are a lot of pigeons and there have been times that the chairs have several markings. 2) it happens to be raining as we are visiting, which we love, but now we can’t go out there since it is all wet.

Otherwise, a great hotel. Definitely recommend.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: I really loved paris , the hotel was nice and the view was awesome , the sweats were very well equiped and the personel was also amazing. The restaurant was also very cool. They had a very good disco bar and the barman was also really nice

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Bathroom is great and the bed is really nice. Wifi is fast and the people are nice. Sometimes it’s very busy in the morning with the breakfast, you have to wait a few minutes when there is a place to sit.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
This is a small hotel at 350m from Line 1 metro station (Porte de Vincennes). Very helpful and kind personnel with a willingness to help. The rooms are clean and bright.
The only disadvantage is the poor breakfast in quantity and variety.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The hotel is very close to a Metro, so easy to go to everywhere. Room are small but nice and normal for France. Good Bathroom, warm bath. The Breakfast was good but they don't have dinner and there no many option around. If you are going on vacation is better to choose another location.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Decent hotel and friendly staff but when the reception requires the credit card that paid for the room in order to check in. That means if you are travelling on business and you did not book the room yourself, you will not be able to check in.
The rooms are small but comfortable, the heating is on too high so you will have to open the window during the day to let it cool down.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Great hotel with a very modern layout at an affordable price. I loved the actual hotel room, especially the bathroom. The hotel staff are very friendly and accommodating. My only conplaint would be that the room is really small but I guess that’s cause space is limited in Paris ! But it was still extremely comfortable to relax or watch tv in.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: we booked this hotel because it was not far from station for taking the train to Disney. Afterwards we found out this was a perfect location to travel around in Paris, taking the metro not far from the hotel.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Hotel is just a 3 min Walk from the Metro station with line directly to arc triomphe, Champs-Elysées, La Défense, jardin tulleries and Louvre. the room was clean and tidy and had a good size for a short stay. Only the arpet seemed a bit old and dirty, a new one wood be great here. Also the bath room was modern and clean. The room service made the bedsheets every day, but didn’t bring out the garbage. Didn’t have breakfast but 14€ seemed a bit to much for us. We had a good stay. Hotel is highly recommended.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Hotel nice and clean, staff friendly. It's not a particularly good neighbourhood, but it's within easy walking distance of an all-night pizza place that is brilliant value for money. For budget accommodation in Paris it's a good choice.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: A very decent little hotel. Great location next to little shops and very close to Metro and tram lines. The room was clean and tidy and each morning there was a good buffet breakfast. The reception staff were helpful.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Really really loved this hotel. The ONLY single problem was parking as none was available at or near the hotel. I know the hotel are not responsible for this but guidance as to local car parks would be a good idea. I would certainly stay here again. In fact, the family has decided to go back again. Soon

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The rooms are extremely smaller than what we were used to!! We only booked one room for myself, my husband and two kids under three. We had to get two rooms just to accommodate us. The fro t desk attendant was very accommodating. He went out of his way to find us rooms near each other for a fair price. He actually made our stay enjoyable. I wish I could remember his name but thank you for great service at check in. Nice full breakfast buffet and great location near public transportation, shops and a park. Quiet area too!! The room is functional yet comfortable.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Hall of the hotel is nice, rooms are with good space and decoration nice, not so far the subway station, good price, calm location in a little street, a few good restaurants at 5 to 10 mn walk. However, the breakfast room is too small so on morning it can be difficult.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Service is good enough but it has a smallbreakfast buffet. Room is quite clean and small and its amenities are complete. Staffs are polite and helpful. location is not in the city center but near to two main line of metro and train with easy access to Charle De Goule and Orly airport.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Nice, quiet and good service. Very close to all public transportation, This place is pecfect place for people who need a good one but can't afford staying in High standard's hotels.
Nice staff at the reception and good manager's initiative.
I had my free Beaujolais, though..! lol!!!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Nice and pleasant stay. It's a comfortable and clean hotel, in a residential area, just a few minutes from the nearest subway station, and close to cafes, restaurants and supermarkets. Staff was very friendly and the price was very fair.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: It's a good hotel to stay in Paris. I've stayed for 2 days with my wife to know the city. The rooms are comfortable and clean. The attendants are polite and solicitous. There is a subway station near to the hotel to get around the city.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The rooms have been recently refurbished and offer a modern, luxury and nice atmosphere. Very quiet rooms, as well as very friendly and cooperative personnel. The hotel is very close to the Nation metro station, to be reached by feet. I can only recommend this hotel to families who want to visit Paris.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Spent 3 nights here on business. Perfectly placed for me to get out to the east but easy to get into the centre of Paris on Line 1. The hotel is on a quiet back street, very warm welcome from the desk staff every time I passed by. I didn’t have the breakfast but it seemed a little pricey. My room was extremely clean, with a comfortable bed, nice and warm and well equipped including a fridge. The free bottle of water was a nice touch. My only minor gripe I’ve got is that in an attempt to fill the room space available, the wardrobe is half size, by that I mean you can’t hang trousers full length and a long shirt touches the top of the fridge/safe. The area is really nice, good restaurants and cafes with tram metro and RER all minutes away. I’ll definitely stay here again.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: We spent here 3 nights during a business trip. Our bedroom was small but clean (there were 2 twin beds) and there was not enough space if 2 people have to stand up at the same time. We used the room service for breakfast one of the 3 days and the food variety was good. Overall a good experience.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: This hotel is perfect for a short stay in Paris. The metro is a two minute walk from the hotel and it is only a 20 minute metro journey to attractions such as the Louvre. The location itself is ideal, somewhat quieter than tourist locations but still very busy with a typically French patisserie just a short walk down the road and a McDonald's across the road. Though the rooms are quite small (and the lift not suitable for more than 2 people), they are very clean and comfortable. The shower is powerful and the beds very comfortable. We were pleasantly surprised to also find a high quality docking station/alarm in our room, suited to an iPhone 4 or older iPhone model. Staff members were helpful and offered to take care of our luggage after check out. We thoroughly enjoyed our stay here and would definitely visit again.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
We stayed here for three nights for a long weekend in Paris. We were greeted by a really nice man at the front desk who was really helpfull and serviceminded.
The room was small, but OK. The bathroom was nice and clean, and the shower was huge. We ate breakfast at the hotel two days, and it was a nice basic breakfast. Worth the price!
The location of the hotel is right around the corner of a metro stop, so getting everywhere is easy.

All in all we had a good stay!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The moment you enter , you see Paul at the front desk. A real jolly , friendly and helping guy. Hotel is minutes away from metro. Rooms are cozy , comfy and good service . There is also a great food area few minutes walk with a lot of Turkish restaurants . Pharmacy is just opposite to the hotel . Overall , great . 5/5

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Set round the corner from the Metro and a cross linking Tram with a Mickey Ds round the corner should budget or kids demand. Breakfast most days has a good selection but self service and with cooling precooked items if your eating after 10. Items available for our first two days were not on offer on Tuesday which had a limited choice still available for us when arriving 30 minutes before Breakfast closes. There is only self service but enough to survive even when less available.
Our 4th floor room , 405. had the basic needs and despite being near the tiny lift had no noise problem and we had restful sleep. Would stay again but eat in Nation or before leaving the Centre of Paris as the local offering can be hit or Miss and that miss could be by Miles .

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
I stayed in this hotel during my visit to Paris. The hotel is small but that's the case with most hotels in Paris. The bed was comfortable and I would recommend the hotel if you are staying for a short trip. It is far from the top attractions but the train station is very close by.
I did not like the fact that I had to pay a deposit for the mini bar, which was quite steep. For some odd reason the machine initially refused to accept my credit card and I had to pay cash, which was quite annoying. There are few eating areas close by.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
The hotel is at a great location. A 3 min walk from the metro 1 station that connects to most of the tourist attractions.

There is a wide variety of restaurants, cafes, a Mc D and a few ethnic cuisine restaurants in the area within walking distance.

Great breakfast spread, comfortable beds and clean bathrooms.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Had a nice time, it's Paris in the summer so it doesn't really matter where you stay, right? But this hotel is small but clean, friendly staff and really has all you need for a weekend break. Admittedly it is a bit off the beaten track but the metro station is a minute walk away and once you're on, the world is your oyster. A key stand out for myself personally was a member of staff by the name of Nessim, a very nice attentive host who looked after us and pushed this stay from a three to a four star. Didn't do the breakfast but there are lovely brasserie's a minute away and supermarkets and tobacco shops on the Main Street.

Rooms are small but washroom is magic, has a minibar and a safe. Scenic views aren't from the window but the Eiffel Tower is only 15 minutes by metro.

They let us bring our own wine onto the back smoking area for a few night caps.

All things considered I'd stay here again.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Clean and cousy hotel in a peacefull neighbourhood!
Close to metro/bus station.
Breakfest buffet not so good.
Onla french TV channels.
Very small wardreobe closet.
Generally I recomend for a short stay in Paris.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Great hotel with charming, clean and comfortable rooms with a nice modern design. The staff was friendly, prof. and very helpful. The breakfast good with many options. It was easy to get around with the metro just around the corner. The perfect hotel for my stay in wonderful Paris!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
We stayed at this hotel for 2 nights for visiting Paris and Disneyland. Overall it was a good hotel with the main benefit being close to the metro station. We bought a travel card from the metro station by the airport for the metro and bus so we could get from the airport (Charles) and to where we need to go throughout our stay. It was 28 euros and 5 euros for the photo on the travel card. We used google maps to get around , taking screenshots of the metro routes and downloading maps. Staff and local people are helpful if you need guidance.

Hotel benefits:

Close to metro

Friendly staff that talk good English
Clean

Free suitcase storage at the before and after checkout

Fast fibre internet

Room safe and hangers , kettle with tea and coffee , couple of milks

They hold your room door card while you are out. This is good so it's not lost but would be good to have the option to take it with you and just pay a fine if it is lost.

Large windows and little balcony

Hotel drawbacks:

Had to pay £50 euros deposit for the mini bar as we didn't have a credit card

Lift can only fit one person and suitcase

Breakfast was expensive (so went over the road to the local bakery that offer bread , qasants and pastries for 1-2 euros and local shop has juices)

The rooms where small but big enough for a weekend , couldn't sit straight on the toilet as it's close to the shower. We had twin beds pushed together rather then a double :( , the beds where slipping on the carpet meaning they kept coming apart.

Overall we would stay again but make sure we got a double room as on the booking it was a double or twin room. Would like to have a room where you can sit normally on the toilet.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Excellent hotel in a fantastic location. The rooms are quite small but perfect and for the price you can't complain. The bed is very comfortable and there is a lovely big shower in the bathroom. Staff are very friendly and helpful if you have any problem. We never had breakfast in the hotel as we preferred to eat out but the area looked lovely and there seemed to be a good selection. In the evening times near the reception desk there was always a basket of pastries I'm assuming left over from breakfast that you could take for free! A lovely wee touch.

Location was ideal. Literally round the corner, a two minute walk, was the metro station that is on one of the main metro lines. Only two stops from Gare de Lyon aswell. Safe location, seemed to be a commuter town, and on the way to metro station was an ATM which was handy. Some excellent fresh fruit shops along the way too.

To summarise, room could be considered small for some people. In my opinion for the middle of Paris it's an excellent size and very comfortable. The price is very good, and the location is hard to beat. Very good value for money! If we are ever in Paris again, will definitely stay here!

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: For the money I paid and a brand hotel, I expected a better experience. The rooms were small, even by Paris standards; the elevator made me feel claustrophobic (only myself and my suitcase could fit - my husband had to wait for it to come back); the walls were thin (we could hear the neighbours); the view from our room was the worst (looking into an alley); we had to submit our key card every time we left the building, a maid knocked the door one morning without saying 'housekeeping' and without pausing and came right in - I had just come out of the shower; and breakfast was overpriced. It was very close to the subway and nice restaurants nearby - only real plus.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
Hotel is convenient, with clean and spacious room.
We were even able to borrow adaptors and get our documents printed as there is a printer available for guests.
Highly recommended, not to mention that I'll book this same hotel for the next visit.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews:
The hotel is rated 4* as it manages to incorporate alot af amenities into small amount of space. The room was small but as advertised. If you have large bags you might have troubles moving in the room.

The door between the corrdior and guestroom could just as well have been shower curtain as there was no sound insulation. Sound insulation between rooms was also below average resulting in waking up early when other people woke up.

Staff was friendly and helpful.

Annoying operational things that the hotel could have prevented
- Toilet bin had not been emptied in the toilet
- Internet code ran out at 23:59 night before checkout.
- A/C was heating only
- They have a mandatory requirement that you leave the key in the reception when you go out of the hotel..

Breakfast was above average.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: The hotel is fab - very modern, clean and comfortable. We slept really well in our room, however it's worth noting that the rooms are quite compact! The showers were brilliant and there is lots to choose from for breakfast.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Hotel and rooms very clean. Friendly staff, good breakfast (incl bacon), good location right beside Metro line 1. Area is quiet at night but a few bars and restaurants a 5/10 min walk away. Rooms are a little small but perfect for a short stay.

hotel: Best Western Plus 61 Paris Nation Hotel
reviews: Just come back from a 5 night stay here and the staff were very friendly and helpful. I had never visited Paris before and they helped me with directions and how to get to the main attractions such as the Eiffel Tower. The room was small but this wasn't a problem the rooms are also very clean. The metro was just around the corner and is easy to locate. There are plenty of restaurants (including a McDonald's) and shops near by. The only minor complaint about this hotel it can be quite noisy at night but wasn't a problem. Overall was a very nice stay and the staff are lovely.
